---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PreRegistrationForm from '../../components/PreRegistrationForm';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import logoImage from '../../assets/logo.png';
---

<Layout title="Credibility Dynamics">
  <main class="bg-white">
    {/* Hero Section */}
    <section class="pt-40 pb-20 px-4 bg-boho-sand/10">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-boho-dark mb-6 uppercase tracking-widest">Credibility Dynamics</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-boho-dark/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto font-sans">
          Most training programs focus on reducing bias or improving communication. We focus on what happens when credibility itself becomes distorted.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Course Details */}
    <section class="py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-boho-clay mb-6 uppercase tracking-wide">The Value Proposition</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-boho-dark/80 leading-relaxed font-sans mb-4">
            This course teaches participants how credibility judgments actually form, how bias and narrative framing distort evaluation, and how to redirect conversations toward information without escalating conflict.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-boho-dark/80 leading-relaxed font-sans">
            Rather than focusing on persuasion or accusation, the course focuses on improving the quality of evaluation and decision-making in difficult environments.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-boho-clay mb-6 uppercase tracking-wide">Course Outcomes</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-4 text-lg text-boho-dark/80 font-sans">
            <li>Identify when credibility is being influenced by non-evidence factors such as authority, emotion, role, or social dynamics.</li>
            <li>Distinguish clearly between what is observed and what is inferred, reducing errors caused by assumption.</li>
            <li>Recognize the purpose of an interaction and adjust your approach accordingly.</li>
            <li>Use neutral, non-confrontational communication strategies to clarify reasoning and reintroduce evidence.</li>
            <li>Maintain cognitive flexibility under stress, avoiding rigid or reactive interpretation.</li>
            <li>Make decisions based on evidence and context, even when information is incomplete or ambiguous.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-boho-sage/10 p-8 border-l-4 border-boho-sage mb-20">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-boho-dark mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">Core Skill of the Course</h3>
          <p class="text-xl text-boho-dark/80 font-sans font-medium">
            Shift conversations away from <span class="text-boho-clay">judging the person</span> and toward <span class="text-boho-clay">evaluating the information</span>.
          </p>
        </div>

        {/* Pre-Registration Form */}
        <div id="register">
          <PreRegistrationForm client:load courseName="Credibility Dynamics" showFeeNotice={true} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
